  "contrast_notes": [
    "Body text neutral.900 on neutral.0 yields ~17:1, far exceeding WCAG 2.2 SC 1.4.3 (4.5:1) for normal text",
    "fg.muted neutral.600 (#475569) on white is ~7.5:1, safe for secondary text; do not use neutral.400 or lighter for text",
    "primary.default blue.600 (#1d4ed8) on white is ~6.3:1, passing for text and UI components (SC 1.4.11)",
    "In dark theme, primary is lightened to blue.300/400 (#60a5fa) because blue.600 lacks contrast on dark surfaces; pair with dark foreground",
    "amber.600 (#b45309) is used instead of a lighter amber for warning text so it passes 4.5:1; the lighter amber.500 is reserved for fills with dark text"
  ],
  "colour_vision_notes": [
    "Status is never encoded by colour alone (SC 1.4.1): success/warning/danger always pair with an icon and text label",
    "The chart palette separates blue, amber, and violet/rose hues that remain distinguishable under deuteranopia and protanopia; verify with a simulator before shipping",
    "Avoid adjacent red/green chart series; the palette orders blue-teal-amber-violet to maximise separation for the most common CVD types"
  ],
  "evidence": [
    "Contrast ratios computed against WCAG 2.2 SC 1.4.3 and 1.4.11 thresholds",
    "Palette structure follows IBM Carbon and Material data-visualisation colour-blind-safe guidance",
    "Neutral ramp aligns with the widely-used Tailwind slate scale for predictable steps"
  ]
}
